24/01/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- The government is hosting a meeting of the South East European Co-operation Process countries' foreign ministers Tuesday (24 January). 
Representatives of EU president Austria and the Stability Pact are also on hand. 
Participants are discussing topics related to strengthening political dialogue and co-operation in the region, EU integration prospects, and the situation in Kosovo.
In other news, a Greek human rights group has urged the government to legalise cremations, despite opposition from the powerful Orthodox Church. 
The National Committee for Human Rights says the ban violates basic human rights and freedoms. 
(MPA, Fena, AP - 23/01/06)
